Preparation
1 Fill a medium saucepan with water and bring to a boil. Aggressively season with salt. Blanch the broccoli in boiling water for about two minutes.

Drain and finely chop the cooked broccoli.

In a mixing bowl, add broccoli, scallions, garlic, cheddar, egg, and bread crumbs. Optional: Add hot sauce of choice. Mix well and chill in the refrigerator for 15-20
minutes.

Preneat oven to 400°F (204°C).
Spray a nonstick baking sheet with nonstick spray. Shape the mixture into tot shapes and spread them evenly on the sheet.
Bake for 8-9 minutes. Flip and then bake for an additional 8—9 minutes on the other side until golden brown.        
